==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Madly
<hw>Mad"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Mad</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>In a mad manner; without reason or
understanding; wildly.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> insanely, crazily, dementedly.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a desperate manner; <as>as, she fought back
<ex>madly</ex></as>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.6</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>intensely; <as>as, she was <ex>madly</ex> in
love</as>.</def> <wns>[wns=3]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> insanely, deadly, deucedly, devilishly.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.6</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madman</ent>⟦br⟧
